When I was learning english, I didn&rsquo;t know how to distinguish between who, whom and whose. So this post i am noting some keywords to remember. Some knowledge has been extracted from www.myenglishpages.com.&quot;
 The main point &ldquo;Who,&rdquo; &ldquo;whom,&rdquo; and &ldquo;whose&rdquo; are all relative pronouns used in English to refer to  people, animals, or things previously mentioned in a sentence.
Info Who is used as the subject of a sentence or clause (refers to the person who is doing the action).
